Use PowerShell Command Properly:

GET
Invoke-WebRequest http://localhost:52956/api/ProductApi -UseBasicParsing
OR shorter:
iwr http://localhost:52956/api/ProductApi -UseBasicParsing

GET 1 Data
Invoke-WebRequest http://localhost:52956/api/ProductApi/1 -UseBasicParsing
OR shorter:
iwr http://localhost:52956/api/ProductApi -UseBasicParsing


POST
Invoke-WebRequest `
  -Uri http://localhost:52956/api/ProductApi `
  -Method POST `
  -Body '{"Name":"Pen","Price":10}' `
  -ContentType "application/json" -UseBasicParsing

PUT
Invoke-WebRequest `
  -Uri http://localhost:52956/api/ProductApi/1 `
  -Method PUT `
  -Body '{"Id":1,"Name":"Pen Updated","Price":15}' `
  -ContentType "application/json"  -UseBasicParsing


DELETE
Invoke-WebRequest `
  -Uri http://localhost:52956/api/ProductApi/1 `
  -Method DELETE -UseBasicParsing
